<p>I have two pandas data frames:</p>  <pre><code>df1     id frid title     1  1    abc     2  1    ddd     3  2    ghc     4  3    frg     5  1    def  df2     frid comment     1    w     2    s     3    e </code></pre>  <p>Now I want to merge these two data frames based on the field <code>frid</code>. In other words, I want to add column <code>comment</code> to <code>df1</code>. How can I do this? I know about <code>join</code> command, but it works differently (<code>df1.join(df2)</code>).</p>  <p>The result should be:</p>  <pre><code>df     id frid title comment     1  1    abc   w     2  1    ddd   w     3  2    ghc   s     4  3    frg   e     5  1    def   w </code></pre>